               <msContents>
                  <summary>Images 1r-164r: Psalter. The midpoint of the Psalms is unmarked. Psalm 151 is the long version. The superscription to the fourth biblical canticle is the usual one. The Song of Songs is in the common version. The Praises of Mary begins with Monday and culminates in Sunday. Illuminations added recently over text. Images 165l-168l: Explanations of Jesus, Fǝkkare ’Iyyäsus, ፋካሬ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ [Prophecy of Jesus when the disciples asked him about the future], written in a different hand of the 20th century. Image 168r: various texts, asmat prayers, pen trials, in an untrained hand. Image 169l: Asmat prayer for the binding of demons.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <textLang/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
